1. Exploration Data Analysis

According to statistical summary, mean and median of numeric variables are not significantly different.

The penguin dataset has 8 variables consist of 3 character variables and 5 numeric variables (including year variable). There are 3 species (Adelie, Gentoo, Chinstrap) for each sex (male and female), 3 islands (Torgersen, Biscoe, Dream). Observation in the penguin dataset was took place in 2007, 2008, and 2009.

There are 344 with the following missing observations:

1.1 Data Distribution

Gentoo’s bill depth, body mass, and flipper length are vary significantly compare to other species. Adelie can be distinguished clearly compare to other species from its bill length.
